text: Headed to a meeting @ noon with the Border Industrial Association to talk about border economic issues – including our important trade relationship with Mexico.

This week I met with @aihec members to discuss advancing the important work done by Tribal colleges, universities & teachers. I’m proud to work with them to ensure Native students gain skills they need to succeed after graduation while embracing their Native languages & cultures.

I voted no on wasting $25B on an offensive wall on our border. I stand with NM families who oppose @POTUS' effort to impose his xenophobic agenda on our state. New Mexicans of all political backgrounds overwhelmingly support DREAMers and oppose a wall in our backyard.

I voted for Coons-McCain, a bipartisan bill to #ProtectDreamers without wasting billions on an offensive wall. @RealDonaldTrump created this crisis for DREAMers. Now @POTUS and Republican leaders are doing everything to stop us from fixing it.

My heart breaks again today at news of the school shooting in Florida. It's long past time for action to stop the gun violence claiming our children's lives. My thoughts are with the community and victims of this tragedy, and I'm so grateful for the first responders on the scene.

The Senate is beginning its immigration debate today, and I'll be fighting every step of the way to protect #DREAMers.
 
Our efforts must reflect America's proud immigrant history and preserve the diversity and opportunity—for all—that is our greatest strength.

#TrumpBudget is an assault on working families, slashing Medicare & Medicaid, repealing #ACA & taking away health care from hundreds of thousands of New Mexicans & millions of Americans. We should be investing in helping working families get ahead, not undercutting their future.

#TrumpBudget would undercut #publiclands protections & wipe out the #LWCF, which funds conservation across America, fuels the $887B outdoor recreation industry & creates jobs. This is an assault on our #NationalParks & #PublicLands, treasured places that belong to all Americans.

We've made important progress in combatting violence against Native women—but there’s a lot of work left to do. I’m co-chairing an Indian Affairs Committee listening session about #VAWA to gather input from Tribes on implementing & improving this landmark legislation. #SOIN2018
Words and images are still hateful and offensive, even when they appear in a cartoon. The @ABQJournal should apologize.

I'm on my way to the Senate floor to call on Congress to pass legislation that protects Special Counsel Mueller from being fired by @realDonaldTrump.

The Special Counsel must be able to do his job, follow the facts, and deliver the American people the answers they deserve.

.@ChrisCoons and @SenJohnMcCain’s bipartisan bill to protect #Dreamers is an example of the sort of compromise deal Congress can pass. @realDonaldTrump needs to stop politicking on xenophobic immigration rhetoric, find a seat at the table and make a deal.

#Dreamers strengthen our communities and our country every day. They are not political pawns—they are real people with jobs, families and aspirations. It’s time for Congress to preserve their dreams, protect their futures and pass the #DreamAct.

The Nunes Memo is the latest in an unprecedented, partisan attack on law enforcement agencies & the Special Counsel. Every American should want to get to the bottom of Russian meddling—so why are @POTUS & some in GOP doing everything they can to interfere with this investigation?
My thoughts and prayers are with everyone involved in this morning’s awful train accident. I’m grateful for the swift action of my colleagues and first responders on the scene.

Tonight, President Trump began by talking about setting aside our differences, yet he delivered a speech filled with hateful rhetoric demonizing immigrants and gave New Mexicans and Americans nothing to suggest he wants to move us from the dangerous course he has set. #SOTU

.@POTUS should use #SOTU to remind Americans that there’s more that unites us than divides us, and that if we really work together we can end the opioid epidemic, protect DREAMers & build the infrastructure local economies need to succeed.

The American people reject President Trump’s xenophobic politics of hate and division, and I will not accept a ‘take it or leave it’ offer on protection for DREAMers. The White House proposal is insulting, not a serious effort to reach a bipartisan consensus. #DreamActNow

I voted no on Alex Azar's nomination. We shouldn't put American families' healthcare decisions in the hands of a former pharma exec who has opposed lowering drug prices & refuses to acknowledge his former industry is to blame for skyrocketing prices that are hurting our families.

Republicans control the House, Senate & White House & they have failed to do their most basic function—keep the government running. Democrats are ready to work with Trump and the GOP leaders on a deal as soon as they're ready to take yes for an answer & end this #TrumpShutdown.

I won't stop working to end this #TrumpShutdown. Democrats are working w/ GOP senators on a bipartisan budget & solution for DREAMers that also meets @POTUS' demands. When Trump decides what he wants & is willing to work on productive solutions, we'll be ready to go instantly.

Responsibility for this #TrumpShutdown is on the shoulders of Republicans and President Trump who control the House, Senate & White House — New Mexicans and the American people need them to show some leadership, come to the table and negotiate in good faith.

Republicans & @POTUS control the House, Senate & White House & the #TrumpShutdown is on the verge of happening because they refused to lead on a responsible budget & failed to accept a bipartisan deal to fulfill promises for DREAMers.

Time is ticking. Democrats are willing to work to avoid this #TrumpShutdown. But @POTUS & the GOP control Congress & the White House. Will they show some leadership & join us in a good budget deal for the military and the middle class?

Let’s be clear: @POTUS is the only one rooting for a #TrumpShutdown. Democrats want a responsible bipartisan budget agreement that gets us off this endless track of damaging CRs & for Trump to honor his commitment to work in a meaningful way to provide protection for DREAMers.

BIG NEWS: With 50 senators in support of restoring #NetNeutrality, we only need ONE more Republican vote to save the free & open internet. @SenateDems have made their position clear, tell @SenateGOP to join us and support @SenatorMarkey's CRA to restore #NetNeutrality.

You've called, emailed, and raised your voice online, urging us to do everything we can to protect the open internet.

I’m proud to support @SenMarkey @SenateDems effort to reverse @realDonaldTrump’s attack on #NetNeutrality.

It's been 100 days since the Congressional GOP let #CHIP expire.
 
That's 100 days of uncertainty and fear for families of the 9 million kids across America who depend on immunizations, prescriptions & doctors visits through CHIP.
 
This is unconscionable and unacceptable.
I won't stop fighting to keep the internet fair and free for everyone—which is why I am cosponsoring @SenMarkey's resolution to restore #NetNeutrality and protect the open internet.
Welcome to the Senate and congratulations on being sworn in today, @SenTinaSmith and @GDouglasJones! I'm looking forward to working with my newest colleagues.

Every week hundreds of Dreamers across the country are losing their protected status because of @POTUS' heartless decision to end #DACA. Congress must act. We have a bill, the Republicans should allow a vote. #DreamActNow
While Republicans are busy rushing their #GOPTaxScam through before the holidays, they are neglecting the 800,000 young people at risk of deportation. We need a #DreamActNow

Dreamers are scared they will be deported from the only country they have ever known. States are running out of money to provide kids’ health insurance. Meanwhile…Republicans are passing a tax cut for millionaires and billionaires. #DreamActNow #FundCHIPNow #GOPTaxScam

Republicans will take a vote on the #GOPtaxscam as early as TOMORROW. But they can still vote it down and choose to work with Democrats on common-sense tax reform to help working families, not just corporations and the super rich. Keep calling and making your voices heard.

We have almost 800,000 young people whose lives, dreams, and future hang in the balance. They are scared, their families are scared, and everything they have worked for is at risk. Tell Congress we need to pass the #DREAMActNow

It's been 75 days since GOP let #CHIP expire which provides health care for 9,000,000 children. Senate GOP made the time to pass tax cuts for millionaires. They’ve voted to open the #ArcticRefuge to drilling. Yet they continue to ignore children's health.

5 years after #SandyHook, congress has made no progress on commonsense gun laws. Just last week, yet another school—this time in #NM—was touched by a devastating act of gun violence. It is long past time to act to prevent gun violence—we owe it to our children & communities.

Today’s vote to repeal #NetNeutrality rules is a major blow to the internet as we know it. @AjitPaiFCC’s legacy will be leading the surrender of the free & open internet to corporations, letting ISPs create internet toll lanes, & stifling online competition, innovation & dynamism

Too many New Mexicans, especially in rural areas, are already stuck in an internet slow lane. We should be working to expand broadband access and bridge the digital divide — not repealing #NetNeutrality rules and destroying essential protections for a free and open internet.

One thing is clear, the internet is an essential aspect of everyday life. It is not a luxury, it has become a necessity and it should remain free and open to every New Mexican and every American. #ProtectNetNeutrality
Who are @FCC Republicans listening to as they dismantle #NetNeutrality? It’s certainly not the millions & millions of Americans pleading with them to keep the internet free & open.

The good, decent candidate won tonight. Thank you Alabamians for putting country over party.  Bienvenido Doug Jones.
The #GOPTaxScam doesn't just raise taxes for middle class families (to pay for tax cuts for the ultra rich), it jeopardizes their health. Here's how:

There is no excuse for leaving almost 800,000 young people's lives, dreams, and future hanging in the balance.
 
It's time for a vote on the #DreamActNow, we can't wait any longer to protect our immigrant youth.

Americans don’t want a tax bill written in secret, cobbled together at the last minute & filled with goodies for special interests. But that’s what we're going to get unless we can defeat the #GOPTaxScam today.
 
Time is running out—call your Senators now & tell them to vote no.

No middle-class family is demanding permanent tax cuts for corporations. They aren’t demanding a bill that drives up their health care premiums. They certainly aren’t demanding a tax INCREASE.
